AB  - This paper examines the changing structure of Mexican imports over the period 1961–1979 and its relationship to the acceleration of imports in 1978–1979. It is found that the more lenient policies adopted by the government in that period seem to be associated with the higher import levels. A review of Mexican policy with respect to foreign trade in 1980 seems to be consistent with the results reported in this paper.
